1. Physical Hard Drive
    --unique name
    --GB


2. Physical Volume
    --each has only ONE physical hard drive (must be created with hard drive)
    --each has a UUID when created
    --can be added to a Volume group
    --unique name


3. Volume Group
    --has UUID
    --User provided unique name
    --list of Physical Volumes and Logical Volumes
    --TOTAL SIZE: add up all PVs
    --AVAILABLE SPACE: subtract each LV


4. Logical Volume
    --size
    --UUID
    --User provided name
    --Associated volume group (CANNOT exist without VG)
    --If there is no space, LV cannot be created
    --If a user tries to create a logical volume FIRST, it should return error because an LV needs to have a Volume Group beforehand













